arguments.prompt:
You are implementing features for a Blazor Web App (Interactive Auto, Global mode with Individual auth) for a logistics company shipment tracker. The project is already scaffolded at `/tmp/sv-a1719b722bcc4f2a85e1b838266083ca/ShipmentTracker/`.

Project structure:
- `ShipmentTracker/` - Server project (hosts app, EF Core, API endpoints)
- `ShipmentTracker.Client/` - Client project (all interactive UI components, pages)
- Solution file: `ShipmentTracker.sln`

Key facts about Auto Global mode:
- Interactive components MUST go in the `.Client` project
- Components cannot access DbContext directly - must use HTTP APIs
- Both Program.cs files must register matching services
- Global interactivity is already configured - no need for `@rendermode` on pages

Current server Program.cs has: Identity, EF Core with SQLite, all render modes configured.
Current client Program.cs has: AuthorizationCore, CascadingAuthenticationState, AuthenticationStateDeserialization.

The existing `Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` uses `IdentityDbContext<ApplicationUser>`.
The existing `Data/ApplicationUser.cs` extends `IdentityUser`.

## What to implement:

### 1. Shared Models (in Client project since both projects reference it)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Models/ShipmentDto.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

public class ShipmentDto
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Status { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string? CustomerEmail { get; set; }
    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}
```

### 2. Service Interface (in Client project)

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/IShipmentService.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public interface IShipmentService
{
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync();
    Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber);
    Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync();
    Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment);
    Task<ShipmentDto> UpdateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment);
}
```
(Add the using for Models at the top.)

### 3. Client-side HTTP implementation

Create `ShipmentTracker.Client/Services/ShipmentHttpService.cs`:
```csharp
using System.Net.Http.Json;
using ShipmentTracker.Client.Models;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Client.Services;

public class ShipmentHttpService(HttpClient httpClient) : IShipmentService
{
    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetAllShipmentsAsync()
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("api/shipments") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto?> GetShipmentByTrackingNumberAsync(string trackingNumber)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.GetAsync($"api/shipments/track/{trackingNumber}");
        if (!response.IsSuccessStatusCode) return null;
        return await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>();
    }

    public async Task<List<ShipmentDto>> GetShipmentsForCustomerAsync()
    {
        return await httpClient.GetFromJsonAsync<List<ShipmentDto>>("api/shipments/my") ?? [];
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> CreateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PostAsJsonAsync("api/shipments", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>())!;
    }

    public async Task<ShipmentDto> UpdateShipmentAsync(ShipmentDto shipment)
    {
        var response = await httpClient.PutAsJsonAsync($"api/shipments/{shipment.Id}", shipment);
        response.EnsureSuccessStatusCode();
        return (await response.Content.ReadFromJsonAsync<ShipmentDto>())!;
    }
}
```

### 4. Server-side Entity

Create `ShipmentTracker/Data/Shipment.cs`:
```csharp
namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class Shipment
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public string TrackingNumber { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Origin { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Destination { get; set; } = string.Empty;
    public string Status { get; set; } = "Pending";
    public string? CustomerEmail { get; set; }
    public DateTime ShippedDate { get; set; }
    public DateTime EstimatedDelivery { get; set; }
    public DateTime? ActualDelivery { get; set; }
    public string? Notes { get; set; }
}
```

### 5. Update ApplicationDbContext

Edit `ShipmentTracker/Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` to become:
```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Identity.EntityFrameworkCore;
using Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore;

namespace ShipmentTracker.Data;

public class ApplicationDbContext(DbContextOptions<ApplicationDbContext> options) : IdentityDbContext<ApplicationUser>(options)
{
    public DbSet<Shipment> Shipments => Set<Shipment>();
}
