- Components cannot access DbContext directly - must use HTTP APIs
- Both Program.cs files must register matching services
- Global interactivity is already configured - no need for `@rendermode` on pages

Current server Program.cs has: Identity, EF Core with SQLite, all render modes configured.
Current client Program.cs has: AuthorizationCore, CascadingAuthenticationState, AuthenticationStateDeserialization.

The existing `Data/ApplicationDbContext.cs` uses `IdentityDbContext<ApplicationUser>`.
The existing `Data/ApplicationUser.cs` extends `IdentityUser`.

